    {
      "id": "kBoJaE4GHBXjferhWc2F4",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 284,
      "y": 97,
      "width": 1079.5,
      "height": 475,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "a0",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1406904307,
      "version": 1407,
      "versionNonce": 1504937121,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1739637169591,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Functional Requirements - \n1. Ability for each node to read/update/write to local DB.\n2. Ability for each node to write a new log based on the action to the journal service.\n3. Journal service, once received the log, should notify to the replicated nodes with a new log entry.\n4. Ability for each node to receive a notification and create the action based on the log entry in its local DB.\n5. Ability for each node to restore the DB if crashed by replaying the log events from Journal Service.\n\nNon-functional requirements - \n1. Nodes should eventually receive data in its local DB - highlighting strong consistency\n2. Reads >> Write\n3. Conflicts should be handled by journal service. \n4. Delivery of log in Journal service should be guaranteed and in order based on timestamp.\n\n\nData Flow - \n\n1. Add an entry about its action to the Journal and get an acknowledgement\n1. Commit to local DB first via transactional guard\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Functional Requirements - \n1. Ability for each node to read/update/write to local DB.\n2. Ability for each node to write a new log based on the action to the journal service.\n3. Journal service, once received the log, should notify to the replicated nodes with a new log entry.\n4. Ability for each node to receive a notification and create the action based on the log entry in its local DB.\n5. Ability for each node to restore the DB if crashed by replaying the log events from Journal Service.\n\nNon-functional requirements - \n1. Nodes should eventually receive data in its local DB - highlighting strong consistency\n2. Reads >> Write\n3. Conflicts should be handled by journal service. \n4. Delivery of log in Journal service should be guaranteed and in order based on timestamp.\n\n\nData Flow - \n\n1. Add an entry about its action to the Journal and get an acknowledgement\n1. Commit to local DB first via transactional guard\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
